sub_title: Senior Advocaat | Senior Associate at Taylor Wessing Netherlands | EU and Dutch competition law | Foreign investment | Consumer law | Compliance
summary:
As a senior associate specialised in competition law, my practice is focused on proceedings before the EU and Dutch competition (and other) authorities and judiciary, as well as advisory work, regarding the application of the EU and Dutch competition law rules (cartel prohibition, prohibition on abuse of a dominant position and merger control) and other matters relating to EU law (e.g. state aid). Frequently involved in (i) foreign investment, consumer law and compliance related matters, (ii) the coordination of multi-jurisdictional merger filings before competition authorities in and outside the European Union, (iii) corporate social responsibility matters, (iv) drafting and negotiating distribution- and license agreements and (v) public procurement cases.
